"{\"uid\": \"qz.com-google-gemini-ai-olympics-ad-dear-sydney-backlash-1851610243\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"Google's latest Olympics-themed ad for its generative artificial intelligence-powered chatbot, Gemini, isdrawing some backlash.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 127, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 0, \"end\": 6, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Google\", \"score\": 0.9999996639544971, \"rank\": 3.346604889915941e-07, \"text\": \"Google\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Google\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Google\"}, {\"begin\": 95, \"end\": 101, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gemini_Awards\", \"score\": 0.9975698381872821, \"rank\": 0.0024360818859049593, \"text\": \"Gemini\", \"types\": [\"Q618779\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gemini_Awards\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gemini_Awards\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In the\\\"Dear Sydney\\\" ad, Gemini generates a letter for a dad helping his daughter write to Olympic gold medal hurdler, Sydney McLaughlin-Levrone.\", \"from\": 129, \"to\": 273, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 141, \"end\": 147, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sydney\", \"score\": 0.9999982906209482, \"rank\": 1.0227966093285264e-06, \"text\": \"Sydney\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sydney\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sydney\"}, {\"begin\": 153, \"end\": 159, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gemini_Awards\", \"score\": 0.9975698381872821, \"rank\": 0.0024360818859049593, \"text\": \"Gemini\", \"types\": [\"Q618779\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gemini_Awards\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gemini_Awards\"}, {\"begin\": 247, \"end\": 253, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sydney\", \"score\": 0.9999982906209482, \"rank\": 1.0227966093285264e-06, \"text\": \"Sydney\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sydney\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sydney\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The father prompts Gemini to: \\\"Help my daughter write a letter telling Sydney how inspiring she is and be sure to mention that my daughter plans on breaking her world record one day.\", \"from\": 274, \"to\": 456, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 293, \"end\": 299, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gemini_Awards\", \"score\": 0.9975698381872821, \"rank\": 0.0024360818859049593, \"text\": \"Gemini\", \"types\": [\"Q618779\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gemini_Awards\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gemini_Awards\"}, {\"begin\": 345, \"end\": 351, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sydney\", \"score\": 0.9999982906209482, \"rank\": 1.0227966093285264e-06, \"text\": \"Sydney\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sydney\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sydney\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"(She says sorry, not sorry.)\\\"\", \"from\": 457, \"to\": 486, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Those who did not appreciate the ad noted how cold an actual AI-generated fan letter would be.\", \"from\": 488, \"to\": 582, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Linda Holmes, the host of NPR's Pop Culture Happy Hour podcast,wrote on Bluesky: \\\"This commercial showing somebody having a child use AI to write a fan letter to her hero SUCKS.\", \"from\": 583, \"to\": 760, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 583, \"end\": 595, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Linda_Holmes\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.373245727136902e-18, \"text\": \"Linda Holmes\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Linda_Holmes\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Linda_Holmes\"}, {\"begin\": 609, \"end\": 612, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NPR\", \"score\": 0.9999999999997726, \"rank\": 2.9041395012862374e-13, \"text\": \"NPR\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q15265344\", \"Q141683\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NPR\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NPR\"}, {\"begin\": 655, \"end\": 662, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bluesky,_Alberta\", \"score\": 0.934115051658946, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Bluesky\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bluesky,_Alberta\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bluesky,_Alberta\"}, {\"begin\": 717, \"end\": 719, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Artificial_intelligence\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.299955181312914e-19, \"text\": \"AI\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Artificial_intelligence\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Artificial_intelligence\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Obviously there are special circumstances and people who need help, but as a general 'look how cool, she did not even have to write anything herself!'\", \"from\": 761, \"to\": 911, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"story, it SUCKS.\", \"from\": 912, \"to\": 928, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Who wants an AI-written fan letter??\\\"\", \"from\": 929, \"to\": 966, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Holmes went on to say that fan letters are \\\"a great way for a kid to learn to write,\\\" and encouraging children to use AI for writing would prevent them from learning how to improve their writing skills.\", \"from\": 968, \"to\": 1170, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 968, \"end\": 974, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sherlock_Holmes\", \"score\": 0.9999055836299974, \"rank\": 9.442528526191391e-05, \"text\": \"Holmes\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sherlock_Holmes\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sherlock_Holmes\"}, {\"begin\": 1086, \"end\": 1088, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Artificial_intelligence\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.299955181312914e-19, \"text\": \"AI\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Artificial_intelligence\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Artificial_intelligence\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Sit down with your kid and write the letter with them!,\\\" Holmes wrote.\", \"from\": 1171, \"to\": 1242, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1229, \"end\": 1235, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sherlock_Holmes\", \"score\": 0.9999055836299974, \"rank\": 9.442528526191391e-05, \"text\": \"Holmes\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sherlock_Holmes\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sherlock_Holmes\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I am just so grossed out by the entire thing.\\\"\", \"from\": 1243, \"to\": 1290, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Meanwhile, members of the Daddit subreddit on Reddit seemed to share the sentiment, with some calling the ad\\\"disgusting\\\" and \\\"tone deaf\\\"for taking creativity and personality out of communication, and for depicting a parent too lazy to teach their child how to write.\", \"from\": 1292, \"to\": 1558, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1338, \"end\": 1344, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Reddit\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Reddit\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Reddit\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Reddit\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Google posted the Gemini ad to YouTube with the comments section turned off.\", \"from\": 1560, \"to\": 1636, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1560, \"end\": 1566, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Google\", \"score\": 0.9999996639544971, \"rank\": 3.346604889915941e-07, \"text\": \"Google\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Google\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Google\"}, {\"begin\": 1578, \"end\": 1584, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gemini_Awards\", \"score\": 0.9975698381872821, \"rank\": 0.0024360818859049593, \"text\": \"Gemini\", \"types\": [\"Q618779\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gemini_Awards\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gemini_Awards\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"On X, formerly Twitter, one viewer described the ad as \\\"heartless,\\\" while another said parents using AI this way would be \\\"doing their child a gross disservice.\\\"\", \"from\": 1637, \"to\": 1798, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1652, \"end\": 1659, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Twitter\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.653830330708533e-27, \"text\": \"Twitter\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Twitter\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Twitter\"}, {\"begin\": 1738, \"end\": 1740, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Artificial_intelligence\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.299955181312914e-19, \"text\": \"AI\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Artificial_intelligence\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Artificial_intelligence\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Even though the ad shows Gemini responding with \\\"a draft\\\" to get the letter-writing process started, TechCrunch's Anthony Ha pointed out thatif all of McLaughlin-Levrone's fans used Geminias a starting point, \\\"Sydney would just end up with a giant stack of nearly identical letters.\\\"\", \"from\": 1800, \"to\": 2083, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1825, \"end\": 1831, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gemini_Awards\", \"score\": 0.9975698381872821, \"rank\": 0.0024360818859049593, \"text\": \"Gemini\", \"types\": [\"Q618779\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gemini_Awards\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gemini_Awards\"}, {\"begin\": 1901, \"end\": 1911, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/TechCrunch\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"TechCrunch\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/TechCrunch\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/TechCrunch\"}, {\"begin\": 2010, \"end\": 2016, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sydney\", \"score\": 0.9999982906209482, \"rank\": 1.0227966093285264e-06, \"text\": \"Sydney\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sydney\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sydney\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Still, it's not as if big-time celebrities are known for actually reading and replying to fan mail personally;some celebrities simply outsource the job.\", \"from\": 2084, \"to\": 2236, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Google ad communications manager Alana Beale told Axios that the company believes \\\"that AI can be a great tool for enhancing human creativity, but can never replace it.\\\"\", \"from\": 2238, \"to\": 2407, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2326, \"end\": 2328, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Artificial_intelligence\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.299955181312914e-19, \"text\": \"AI\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Artificial_intelligence\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Artificial_intelligence\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Although a different use-case, Gemini isone of the most-used AI toolsat work, according to FlexOS.\", \"from\": 2409, \"to\": 2507, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2440, \"end\": 2446, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gemini_Awards\", \"score\": 0.9975698381872821, \"rank\": 0.0024360818859049593, \"text\": \"Gemini\", \"types\": [\"Q618779\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gemini_Awards\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gemini_Awards\"}, {\"begin\": 2470, \"end\": 2472, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Artificial_intelligence\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.299955181312914e-19, \"text\": \"AI\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Artificial_intelligence\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Artificial_intelligence\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In May, a survey by Microsoft and LinkedIn found thatthree in four workers are using generative AIin the workplace.\", \"from\": 2508, \"to\": 2623, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2528, \"end\": 2537, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Microsoft\", \"score\": 0.9999999946608114, \"rank\": 3.3082252576620603e-09, \"text\": \"Microsoft\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Microsoft\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Microsoft\"}, {\"begin\": 2542, \"end\": 2550, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/LinkedIn\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"LinkedIn\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/LinkedIn\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/LinkedIn\"}]}]}"